Text.text: Just wait until you get older. In high school you’ll have more options. Especially if you keep getting grades like this!
you take the SATs in middle school. you do really well, and now you’re qualified to go to a special sleep-away camp.
Sure, Grier has higher grades than you, but is she taking any honors classes? I mean, besides French. French hardly counts.
your mom teaches you a song to help you memorize your phone number. this will help in kindergarten admission interviews.

Every night before a biology test, Jenna invites you over to her house to study. you teach her the entire unit, and you both get As.
'She has trouble focusing in class — she’s just so bored. they caught her reading a book under the table. At least she’s reading, right?'
Everyone just want to make sure you’re well rounded. Sometimes your mother asks you if you’re under too much pressure. You don’t know what she’s talking about.
you learn to read before any of your friends
